In[117]:
def load_and_prepare(file_path, date_format=None):
    df = pd.read_csv(file_path)
    first_col = df.columns[0]
    df.rename(columns={first_col: 'Date'}, inplace=True)
    df['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Date'], format=date_format, errors='coerce').dt.date
    df.dropna(subset=['Date'], inplace=True)
    return df

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

sns.set(style='whitegrid', palette='deep', font_scale=1.1)
fig, axes = plt.subplots(3, 2, figsize=(18, 16))

# Inflation
sns.lineplot(ax=axes[0, 0], data=inflation, marker='o')
axes[0, 0].set_title('Inflation (alle Werte)')
axes[0, 0].legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.02, 1), loc='upper left')

# Geopolitical Risk
sns.lineplot(ax=axes[0, 1], data=geopolitical_risk, marker='o', color='r')
axes[0, 1].set_title('Geopolitical Risk (alle Werte)')
axes[0, 1].legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.02, 1), loc='upper left')

# Goldpreis
sns.lineplot(ax=axes[1, 0], data=gold_price, marker='o', color='gold')
axes[1, 0].set_title('Goldpreis (alle Werte)')
axes[1, 0].legend(bbox_to_anchor=(1.02, 1), loc='upper left')

# Interest Rates

axes[1, 1].set_title('Interest Rates (alle Werte)')

In[131]:
def plot_correlation_matrix(df, title="Korrelationsmatrix", figsize=(10, 8)):
    """
    Zeigt eine Korrelationsmatrix-Heatmap fr einen gegebenen DataFrame an.

    Parameter:
    - df: DataFrame mit numerischen Werten
    - title: Titel der Heatmap
    - figsize: Gre der Grafik
    """
    plt.figure(figsize=figsize)
    corr = df.corr(numeric_only=True)

    sns.heatmap(
        corr,
        annot=True,
        fmt=".2f",
        cmap="coolwarm",
        square=True,
        annot_kws={"size": 10},
        cbar_kws={"shrink": 0.8},
        linewidths=0.5,
        linecolor='gray'
    )
    plt.title(title, fontsize=14)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right', fontsize=9)
    plt.yticks(rotation=0, fontsize=9)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

In[166]:
delta = merged_df['Gold_Ajclose'].diff()

# Positive und negative Bewegungen isolieren
gain = delta.clip(lower=0)
loss = -delta.clip(upper=0)

# Gleitender Durchschnitt ber 14 Tage
window = 14
avg_gain = gain.rolling(window=window, min_periods=window).mean()
avg_loss = loss.rolling(window=window, min_periods=window).mean()

# Verhltnis berechnen
rs = avg_gain / avg_loss

# RSI berechnen
merged_df['RSI_14'] = 100 - (100 / (1 + rs))
print(merged_df[['Gold_Ajclose', 'RSI_14']].tail(20))

def extract_price_adjclose_columns(df):
    """
    Erstellt eine Kopie des DataFrames und gibt eine neue Kopie zurck,
    die nur die Spalten enthlt, deren Name 'price', 'adj close' oder 'ajclose' enthlt.
    Gro-/Kleinschreibung wird ignoriert, Unterstriche und Leerzeichen werden gleich behandelt.
    """
    df_copy = df.copy()
    patterns = ['price', 'adj close', 'ajclose']
    selected_cols = [
        col for col in df_copy.columns
        if any(pat in col.lower().replace('_', ' ') for pat in patterns)
    ]
    return df_copy[selected_cols]

In[177]:
def add_pct_change_columns(df):
    """
    Fr jede numerische Spalte im DataFrame wird eine neue Spalte erstellt,
    die die prozentuale Tagesvernderung (Rendite) enthlt.
    Die neue Spalte hat den Suffix '_pct_change'.
    """
    df_copy = df.copy()
    for col in df_copy.columns:
        df_copy[f"{col}_pct_change"] = df_copy[col].pct_change()
    return df_copy

In[179]:
def replace_price_columns_with_pct_changes(base_df):
    price_df = extract_price_adjclose_columns(base_df)
    price_changes_df = add_pct_change_columns(price_df)
    base_cleaned = base_df.drop(columns=price_df.columns)
    new_price_cols = [col for col in price_changes_df.columns if col.endswith('_pct_change')]
    renamed_cols = {
        col: col.replace(' ', '_').replace('_pct_change', '_pct') for col in new_price_cols
    }
    price_changes_renamed = price_changes_df[new_price_cols].rename(columns=renamed_cols)
    result_df = pd.concat([base_cleaned, price_changes_renamed], axis=1)
    return result_df
